  "description": "The Ferrari 360 Modena, produced from 1999 to 2005, is powered by a naturally aspirated 3.6-litre V8 producing 394 bhp. The 360 introduced Ferrari's aluminium space-frame construction and represented a significant leap in design from its predecessor, the F355. Manual gearbox examples and the lightweight Challenge Stradale variant are the most sought-after by collectors."
